    • Method Detail

      • clone

        public static ColumnComparableTuple clone(ColumnComparableTuple t)
        Creates a deep and hard copy of a tuple object t. Neither the pointer to the copy of t nor the pointer of t's components are identical to the original object t. This ensures modifications of t will not effect it's copies.
        Parameters:
        t - The tuple to copy
        Returns:
        A tuple identical to t which is independent of t with respect to t's references.

      • project

        public static ExtendedResultSetMetaData project(ExtendedResultSetMetaData metaData,
                                                int[] columns)
                                         throws SQLException,
                                                IllegalArgumentException,
                                                IndexOutOfBoundsException
        An unary operation where columns is an array of column indices. The result of this operation is a subset of metaData in which other attributes (column indices) than columns are discarded (or excluded).

        Note: The first column index is 1 not 0.
        Parameters:
        metaData - The source meta data
        columns - Array of indices which represents attribute columns and which should be keep in the result.
        Returns:
        A subset of metaData which is clipped to the given columns. Note: This operation does not change the original object. Instead it returns a new object which is a subset of the original object.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If columns is empty or at least one components is lesser than 1. This exception will be also thrown if a projection column is set twice or more in columns.
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - If columns contains more (unique) indices than the dimension of this tuple is or if at least one component of columns is out of bounds.
        SQLException - If it fails to work with the underlying ResultSetMetaData

      • project

        public static Tuple project(Tuple tuple,
                            int[] columns)
                     throws IllegalArgumentException,
                            IndexOutOfBoundsException
        An unary operation where columns is an array of column indices. The result of this operation is a subset of tuple in which other attributes (column indices) than columns are discarded (or excluded).

        Note: The first column index is 1 not 0.
        Parameters:
        tuple - The source tuple
        columns - Array of indices which represents attribute columns and which should be keep in the result.
        Returns:
        A subset of tuple which is clipped to the given columns. Note: This operation does not change the original object. Instead it returns a new object which is a subset of the original object.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If columns is empty or at least one components is lesser than 1. This exception will be also thrown if a projection column is set twice or more in columns.
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - If columns contains more (unique) indices than the dimension of this tuple is or if at least one component of columns is out of bounds.
